article.headline: Drexel 57, William & Mary 46
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Frank Elegar scored 17 points to lead Drexel to a 57-46 win over William & Mary on Thursday night. The Dragons (9-5, 3-0 Colonial Athletic Association) went on a 14-2 run within the first eight minutes, ending the first half leading 23-18. The Tribe (5-7, 0-3) took its only lead at 37-34 with 10:57 to play on consecutive layups by Brian Hutt and Adam Payton, but Bashir Mason's 3-pointer tied it and sparked a 13-2 run for the Dragons that put them in control to stay. William & Mary went 3-for-10 from the field in the last 3:16. Kenell Sanchez added 13 points for Drexel, and Mason had 11. Hutt led the Tribe with 12 points and 10 rebounds, and Laimis Kisielius scored 11.
